HEADWORD: boardwalk
<hw>board"walk</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a walkway made of wooden boards;
usually at a seaside. The more elaborate boardwalks at shore resorts are
lined with many commercial retail establishments, on the side of the
walk opposite the ocean.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧On the Boardwalk in Atlantic
City⟦rdquo⟧⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

